.TH "dma_buf_set_name" 9 "dma_buf_set_name" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dma_buf_set_name \- Set a name to a specific dma_buf to track the usage. The name of the dma-buf buffer can only be set when the dma-buf is not attached to any devices. It could theoritically support changing the name of the dma-buf if the same piece of memory is used for multiple purpose between different devices.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "long" dma_buf_set_name
.BI "(struct dma_buf *dmabuf "  ","
.BI "const char __user *buf "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dmabuf" 12
[in]     dmabuf buffer that will be renamed.
.IP "buf" 12
[in]     A piece of userspace memory that contains the name of
the dma-buf.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns 0 on success. If the dma-buf buffer is already attached to
devices, return -EBUSY.
